ometimes anti-disciplinary) linguistic science of gender and sexuality. In three sections, it respectively considers the development of hyper-speciated queer linguistic subfields, the interdisciplinarity of intersectional approaches to queer language, and the institution of queer linguistic science both within and beyond the academy. Taken together, the essays in this collection confront the scientific and institutional discipline of linguistics from a queer vantage point, one which is perhaps inherently interdisciplinary in its formulation.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aPostcolonialism. 0aQueer theory. 4aGeschlechterforschung & Sexualität. 4aInterdisziplinarität. 4aQueer Linguistics. 4aQueer Theorie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGender and Sexuality.  aQueer Linguistics.  aQueer Theory.1 aBarrett, Rusty, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalder, J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCanning, Dominique A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHall, Kira, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKibbey, Tyler Everett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKibbey, Tyler Everett, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKonnelly, Lex, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeap, William, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMararac, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCleary, Bryce, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVanderStouwe, Chris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWang, Ping-Hsuan, econtrib